uthoritative while avoiding broad upstream test dependencies if possible. I’m also thinking about whether `agent_guidance` is specifically asking for \\\"environment/system property/test setup guidance.\\\" I just need to ensure the final output is a valid JSON object!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Meaningful coverage of doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 usually requires its Maven/Sisu component wiring plus parser modules that are test-scoped in the upstream POM, not pulled in by the normal scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 marks maven-artifact as provided, but core public skin APIs use Artifact/DefaultArtifact when creating SiteRenderingContext for a skin.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Upstream explicitly notes parser modules are no longer in doxia-core and must be stated so component descriptors are picked up; APT is a normal Doxia site source format.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-xdoc:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"XDOC rendering is a normal site-renderer path and is test-scoped upstream, so the generated scaffold will not receive its parser component transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-fml:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"FML/FAQ rendering is a normal site-renderer path and is test-scoped upstream, so the generated scaffold will not receive its parser component transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-testing:1.4.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"DefaultSiteRenderer has injected Doxia, ParserModuleManager, VelocityComponent, and PlexusContainer fields; upstream tests obtain SiteRenderer from a Plexus test container instead of direct construction.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment/system property is indicated. Tests should account for the 2.0.0 API changes: use DocumentRenderingContext instead of the removed RenderingContext, avoid removed logging/default-template setters, and obtain SiteRenderer through component lookup or otherwise initialize its injected collaborators before exercising render/locate/merge paths. Create temporary site and skin resources in test code.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 1.9.1 tests fail javac primarily because public APIs changed in 2.0.0; setup alone will not fix those source incompatibilities.\",\n    \"Parser-module component discovery and Velocity/Sisu wiring may affect native-image behavior, so local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06a9da576cf1b926016a3f62d20b0c8197ad77022bd7b2b72d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 900, "output": 978, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51542, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782538954009, "responseId": "resp_06a9da576cf1b926016a3f62cac2c88197be16f136623d494e"}}
